# Slidev Presentation Guidelines for Interns
## Preventing Content Overflow & Creating Professional Slides

### Text Content Rules
1. **Keep it short**: 
   - Maximum 5-7 words per bullet point
   - No more than 4-5 bullet points per slide
   - Break complex ideas into multiple slides

2. **Text sizing hierarchy**:
   - Headers: text-2xl to text-4xl (use sparingly)
   - Main content: text-base to text-lg
   - Descriptions/captions: text-xs to text-sm
   - Add `leading-tight` to reduce line spacing

3. **Content padding**:
   - Leave 10% margin on all sides of content
   - Use `p-2 sm:p-3 md:p-4` for responsive padding

### Mermaid Diagram Guidelines
1. **Size control**:
   - Always set `scale: 0.7` or `scale: 0.8` (never higher)
   - Set `theme: 'neutral'` for consistent styling

2. **Content limitations**:
   - Maximum 5-7 nodes total
   - Keep node labels under 8 characters
   - Use simple connection lines (avoid complex branching)
   - Prefer `graph LR` (left-right) over `graph TD` (top-down)

3. **Styling simplification**:
   - Use custom classes sparingly (max 1-2)
   - Avoid nested subgraphs when possible

### Code Slide Guidelines
1. **Line limits**:
   - Show no more than 16 lines per slide
   - Use line highlighting to stage attention across steps
2. **Split long code**:
   - Split into multiple slides or use `<v-clicks>` with separate code blocks
3. **Sizing**:
   - Prefer `text-sm` or `text-base` for code, maintain readability

### Responsive Width & Typography
- Constrain content width with `max-w-3xl mx-auto`
- Use `text-base md:text-lg leading-tight` for main content
- Add vertical rhythm with `space-y-2`

### Reveals & Pacing
- Use `<v-click>` or `<v-clicks>` to reveal groups of content
- Avoid revealing every single bullet individually unless necessary

### Responsive Layout Formula (Always Use These)
1. **Grid patterns**:
   ```html
   <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-2 sm:gap-3 md:gap-4">
     <!-- Content here -->
   </div>
   ```

2. **Two-column layout**:
   ```html
   <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 items-center">
     <div><!-- Left content --></div>
     <div><!-- Right content --></div>
   </div>
   ```

3. **Element sizing**:
   ```html
   <span class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl">Title</span>
   <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm md:text-base">Description</p>
   ```

### Content Limits by Component Type
| Component | Small Screen | Medium Screen | Large Screen |
|-----------|--------------|---------------|--------------|
| Icons     | Max 3        | Max 6         | Max 9        |
| Grid cells | Max 4       | Max 6         | Max 9        |
| Diagram nodes | Max 4    | Max 6         | Max 8        |
| Text lines | Max 6       | Max 8         | Max 10       |

